commitResults.messageBody:
ClearCommand currently clears the entire address book without
considering any specifications by the user.

This will not support our MVP specifications for the clear command to
take in tags or filters to clear by.

Let's add a ClearCommandParser to provide future parsing support when
we add the functionality for ClearCommand in the future.

The ClearCommandParser uses similar logic to the FindCommandParser, except
throwing an error when the arguments is empty. This is to allow the original
command to still take place.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix issues with tests and checkstyle

commitResults.messageBody:
There is currently no Predicate class for identifying Persons
whose attributes may match any of the keywords or search query given.

Let's add a new Predicate class PersonContainsKeywordsPredicate
which first checks the search query for what keywords to check
in which attribute categories.

The Predicate's test method then checks a Person if any of their
attributes matches any of the specified keywords.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update ClearCommand to accept filter queries
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, ClearCommand will clear all data without considering any
filters.

Let's add functionality for the ClearCommand to take in a
PersonContainsKeywordsPredicate and filter and clear based on that
predicate.
